{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:d","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"double"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"zoomLevel"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition to affecting the visual size and detail of features on the map,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the zoom level affects the size of the vector tiles that are loaded. At zoom","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"level 0, each tile covers the entire world map; at zoom level 1, it covers ¼","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the world; at zoom level 2, ","type":"text"},{"text":"1","type":"text"},{"text":"⁄","type":"text"},{"text":"16","type":"text"},{"text":" of the world, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so on.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Changing the value of this property updates the map view immediately. If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"want to animate the change, use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-setZoomLevel:animated:"},{"text":" method instead.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The zoom level of the receiver."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/zoomlevel"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/d